abstract: Gale Gillingham, former All-Pro guard for the Green Bay Packers who played in Vince Lombardi’s last games as the team’s coach, dies at age 67.
snippet: Gillingham made the Pro Bowl five times in six years and started in Vince Lombardi’s final two games as coach of the team: the storied Ice Bowl and Super Bowl II.
lead_paragraph: Gillingham made the Pro Bowl five times in six years and started in Vince Lombardi’s final two games as coach of the team: the storied Ice Bowl and Super Bowl II.

headline.main: Gale Gillingham, Green Bay Packers’ All-Pro Guard, Is Dead at 67
